2 HOUSE BILL 65
1 WHEREAS, Community health workers play invaluable roles in our public health
2 care system and in Maryland’s diverse communities; and
3 WHEREAS, Community health workers utilize vital cultural and linguistic skills to
4 better serve communities across Maryland in effective, culturally specific ways; and
5 WHEREAS, Community health workers share resources and education about
6 disease prevention and management and help to remove obstacles to community members’
7 health and wellness; and
8 WHEREAS, Community health workers address the social determinants of health
9 and improve health outcomes for low–income, underrepresented, and underserved
10 communities; and
11 WHEREAS, Community health workers strive to ensure that every Marylander has
12 the opportunity to attain their highest level of health; now, therefore,
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That Section(s) 7–410 through 7–421 of Article – General Provisions of the Annotated Code
15 of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 7–411 through 7–422, respectively.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
17 as follows:
18 Article – General Provisions
19 7–410.
20 (A) THE GOVERNOR ANNUALLY SHALL PROCLAIM MAY 8 AS COMMUNITY
21 HEALTH WORKER APPRECIATION DAY.
22 (B) THE PROCLAMATION SHALL URGE EDUCATIONAL AND CULTURAL
23 ORGANIZATIONS TO OBSERVE COMMUNITY HEALTH WORKERS WITH INFORMATIVE
24 PROGRAMS AND ACTIVITIES.
25 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
26 October 1, 2025.

